This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using dependency trees, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a novel approach to NER using global structured information of dependency trees, which involves machine learning techniques such as semi-Markov conditional random fields and guided learning and inference. Therefore, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG), "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI), "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE), and "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR).
